resolution: The European Union should join the Belt and Road Initiative.
The benefits of the United States federal government’s use of offensive cyber operations outweigh the harms.
The United States should end its economic sanctions against Venezuela.
The United States should replace means-tested welfare programs with a universal basic income.
The United States should increase its use of nuclear energy for commercial energy production.
The United States should remove nearly all of its military presence in the Arab States of the Persian Gulf.
The United States federal government should enact the Medicare-For-All Act of 2019.
The United States should adopt a declaratory nuclear policy of no first use.
The National Security Agency should end its surveillance of U.S. citizens and lawful permanent residents.
On balance, the benefits of urbanization in West Africa outweigh the harms.
On balance, the benefits of creating the United States Space Force outweigh the harms.
The benefits of the International Monetary Fund outweigh the harms.
The North Atlantic Treaty Organization should substantially increase its defense commitments to the Baltic states.
Increased United States federal regulation of cryptocurrency transactions and/or assets will produce more benefits than harms.
The United States federal government should legalize all illicit drugs.
On balance, Turkey’s membership is beneficial to the North Atlantic Treaty Organization.
In the United States, the benefits of increasing organic agriculture outweigh the harms.
Japan should revise Article 9 of its Constitution to develop offensive military capabilities.
The United States Federal Government should substantially increase its investment in high-speed rail.
The United States’ strategy of Great Power Competition produces more benefits than harms.
The United States Federal Government should increase its diplomatic efforts to peacefully resolve internal armed conflicts in West Asia.
In the United States, right-to-work laws do more harm than good.
The Republic of India should sign the Artemis Accords.
The United States Federal Government should ban the collection of personal data through biometric recognition technology.
